SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1235
By Akbari
A RESOLUTION to honor Senior Deputy Attorney General Scott
Sutherland on the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to an attorney for the State of Tennessee who has devoted his career to public service; and
WHEREAS, Senior Deputy Attorney General Scott Sutherland earned a Bachelor of Arts
degree from Georgetown College and a Juris Doctor degree from the University of Kentucky
College of Law; and
WHEREAS, he first distinguished himself in public service to the Commonwealth of
Kentucky, pursuing justice without fear or favor as an Assistant Attorney General; in 2011, he
joined the Office of the Tennessee Attorney General and Reporter as a member of the Criminal
Appeals Division; and
WHEREAS, he has subsequently served as Deputy Attorney General of the Law
Enforcement and Special Prosecutions Division and Senior Deputy Attorney General of the Civil
Law Section; and
WHEREAS, throughout his fifteen years of service to the State of Tennessee, General
Sutherland has distinguished himself as an exceptional lawyer and leader; and
WHEREAS, he has diligently selected and developed outstanding attorneys, many of
whom still serve the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, General Sutherland has set a profound standard of kindness and
respectfulness in his interactions with his colleagues, subordinates, and those against whom he
has litigated, regardless of their power, importance, or political party; and
SJR1235
018331
- 1 -

WHEREAS, General Sutherland has tirelessly placed the interests of the State of
Tennessee above his own, regularly sacrificing personal and family time when his duties
exceeded regular working hours; and
WHEREAS, General Sutherland has protected the interests of justice and the rights of
victims by defending the convictions and sentences of many of Tennessee's most violent
criminals; and
WHEREAS, he has scrupulously safeguarded public trust in government by investigating
public corruption and misconduct; and
WHEREAS, General Sutherland has protected the will of Tennesseans by defending the
laws passed by their elected representatives, and he has earned the respect of the federal and
State jurists before whom he practiced and the many lawyers in Tennessee against whom he
litigated; and
WHEREAS, General Sutherland is renowned for his judgment among his peers; his
excellence as a lawyer and his value as a public servant have been duly recognized, as he was
honored with the Attorney General and Reporter's 2023 William M. Leech Jr. Award; and
WHEREAS, the State of Tennessee and its many agencies and officials have benefited
invaluably from General Sutherland's representation and his unhesitating commitment to truth
and justice; and
WHEREAS, General Sutherland is retiring from his duties at the end of the fiscal year;
we acknowledge that although his office may be filled, he can never truly be replaced; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Senior Deputy Attorney General Scott
Sutherland on the occasion of his retirement from service, salute his fifteen years spent
- 2 - 018331

safeguarding the interests of the State of Tennessee, and extend to him our best wishes for a
happy and fulfilling retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
